fields.name: Wands
fields.description: The suit of Wands represents creativity and action.

fields.name: Cups
fields.description: The suit of Cups represents emotions and relationships.

fields.name: Swords
fields.description: The suit of Swords represents intellect and conflict.

fields.name: Pentacles
fields.description: The suit of Pentacles represents material aspects and prosperity.

fields.name: Major Arcana
fields.description: The Major Arcana represents life's major themes and archetypes.

fields.name: Ace of Wands
fields.reversed_meaning: Delays, lack of motivation, or missed opportunities.
fields.description: The Ace of Wands represents a spark of inspiration and creative potential.

fields.name: The Fool
fields.description: The Fool represents the start of a new journey, filled with endless possibilities.

fields.name: The Magician
fields.reversed_meaning: Manipulation, poor planning, or latent talents.
fields.description: The Magician symbolizes resourcefulness and the ability to turn visions into reality.

fields.name: Two of Cups
fields.description: The Two of Cups signifies partnerships and emotional connections.

fields.name: Ace of Swords
fields.description: The Ace of Swords represents intellectual clarity and decisive actions.

fields.name: Ace of Pentacles
fields.reversed_meaning: Financial loss, missed opportunities, or instability.
fields.description: The Ace of Pentacles represents material and financial blessings.
